Correa took the opportunity to reaffirm himself as a defender of press freedom and clarified that what he does not tolerate is “mediocrity, bad faith and lies, which distort freedom of expression.”
“The biggest enemies of press freedom are not evil and perverse politicians, but bad journalists based on profit, blackmail and extortion,” he said.
